<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Rules" content-collection-id="NYCrules" source-infobase-title="The Rules of the City of New York" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\NYCrules.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCrules_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCrules_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-139665" number="109083" version="2548">
			<HEADING>Chapter 14: Requests for Rulemaking</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-18104" name="T63C014"/>Chapter 14: Requests for Rulemaking</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-139667" number="109084" version="2548">
								<HEADING>§ 14-01 Purpose.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-18106" name="T63C014_14-01"/>§ 14-01 Purpose.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139690" number="109085" version="2548">
									<PARA>These rules govern the procedures by which members of the public may submit to the Landmarks Preservation Commission Requests for Rulemaking pursuant to Section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1043" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1043</LINK>(g) of the New York City Charter (City Administrative Procedures Act) and the procedures for the Landmarks Preservation Commission&apos;s consideration and disposition of such Requests. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139689" number="109086" version="2548">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/20/2023, eff. 8/19/2023) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-139693" number="109087" version="2548">
								<HEADING>§ 14-02 Definitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-18108" name="T63C014_14-02"/>§ 14-02 Definitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139688" number="109088" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Commissioners.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Commissioners&quot; means the Commissioners of the Landmarks Preservation Commission. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139687" number="109089" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Person.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Person&quot; means an individual, partnership, corporation or other legal entity, and any individual or entity acting in a fiduciary or representative capacity. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139686" number="109090" version="2550">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Request.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Request&quot; means a request to the Chair of the LPC to consider promulgating a rule. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139685" number="109091" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Requester.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Requester&quot; means a person who has made a request for rulemaking pursuant to this Chapter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139684" number="109092" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Rule.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Rule&quot; has the same meaning as in Section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1041" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1041</LINK>(5) of the New York City Charter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139683" number="109093" version="2550">
									<PARA>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Rulemaking.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Rulemaking&quot; means the process for considering and, if approved, enacting a rule. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139682" number="109094" version="2548">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/20/2023, eff. 8/19/2023) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-139692" number="109095" version="2548">
								<HEADING>§ 14-03 Procedures for Submission of Requests for Rulemaking.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-18110" name="T63C014_14-03"/>§ 14-03 Procedures for Submission of Requests for Rulemaking.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139681" number="109096" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any person may submit a request in writing on a form to be developed and posted on the LPC Website. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139680" number="109097" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The request must include: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139679" number="109098" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The proposed rule to be considered, with proposed language for adoption; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139678" number="109099" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The requester&apos;s arguments in support of adoption of the rule; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139677" number="109100" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The name, address, telephone number, and email address of the requestor or his or her authorized representative. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139676" number="109101" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The request must be submitted by mail addressed to General Counsel, Landmarks Preservation Commission at the LPC&apos;s current mailing address as set forth in the request form, or by electronic mail to rulecomments@lpc.nyc.gov. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139675" number="109102" version="2548">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/20/2023, eff. 8/19/2023) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-139691" number="109103" version="2548">
								<HEADING>§ 14-04 Procedures for Consideration and Response to Requests for Rulemaking.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-18112" name="T63C014_14-04"/>§ 14-04 Procedures for Consideration and Response to Requests for Rulemaking.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139674" number="109104" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>After a complete request is submitted the LPC will take the following steps to process and review: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139673" number="109105" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Acknowledge receipt of the request within 10 business days; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139672" number="109106" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Within 60 business days from the date the complete request was received, the Chair of the Commission will: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139671" number="109107" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(i)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Deny the request. The reasons for the denial will be set forth in writing; or <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139670" number="109108" version="2548">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(ii)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Grant the request. If the request is granted, the Chair will explain in writing the intention to initiate rulemaking by a specified date. The Chair is not required to initiate rulemaking on the entirety of a request or to follow the wording of a request that has been granted. Granting of the request shall only require the Chair to ask the Commissioners to vote to calendar the proposed rule, as proposed by the Chair, and, if there is a positive vote to calendar, for the Commission to hold a public hearing on the proposed rule. Granting of the request does not guarantee that the requested rule will in fact be calendared or approved and adopted by the Commissioners. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-139668" number="109109" version="2548">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/20/2023, eff. 8/19/2023) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-088]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
</DOCUMENT>